A widow is nursing injuries at a hospital after she was attacked allegedly over land. The woman, 57, a resident of Osure Legio village in Ndhiwa, Homa Bay County, was attacked by four men, who injured her on the right shoulder, wrist, and back. ALSO READ:

Conmen sold inheritance of former varsity chief's widow The men were said to have raided the widow's house and dragged her to a nearby bush, where they beat her, leaving her for dead. The attackers then torched her house. Area chief Christopher Milewa said the woman was found abandoned in a bush. Police are looking for the assailants.